<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>•</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence from the Police and Crime Commissioner for South Wales [CST0045]</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">What, if any, targets do you set for your police force? What impact do you think this has on police recording crime practices?</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> 2013/14</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> targets for South Wales Police were set against the background of the very short timescales I had to prepare and publish my Police and Crime Reduction Plan. Current targets are based on supporting the delivery of the plan and provide a clear line of sight</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> through the Force Delivery Plan to divisional and departmental plans within South Wales Police.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">However, since being elected I have been able to review the process and a revised</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> performance monitoring framework</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> has been developed as a joint approach with</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the Chief Constable, taking careful consideration of the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">statutory requirements</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> of not just holding him to account, but also the accountability of partners within the Criminal Justice System, and the partnership landscape as a whole. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">This has led to a m</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ore mature approach to monitoring performance, because the priorities within the Police and Crime Reduction Plan cover a variety of areas and it is apparent that the responsibility for delivery of the plan does not fall at the door of the police alone.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Thi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s has produced a more dynamic, co-operative and layered approach, providing clear accountability for delivering priorities and responsibility for the provision of performance information.  It is not just about targets but also about getting behind the figu</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">res to understand trends, context and accountability and, most importantly, to ensure that activity is driven by the need to deliver high quality and consistent services to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">he public.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">There are a number of key elements to this approach. The first is the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">establishment of my Commissioner’s Strategic Board, which meets monthly and the minutes are made public.  Performance monitoring is a standing agenda item.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Reporting to the Strategic Board is a newly established Joint Performance Management Group, attende</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">d by my Deputy and Assistant Commissioners,  , which has become the keystone for driving the evolution towards a new performance management framework. It is responsible for scrutinising performance and identifying any areas that need to be escalated to the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Strategic Board for further discussion. This joint approach provides an opportunity for the Commissioner’s and Chief Constable’s leadership teams to develop a positive dialogue on understanding the issues behind the figures, and resolving performance issu</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">es</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Another key component is an agreed programme of thematic reviews which will focus on specific areas to provide a greater understanding of issues. These reviews will involve “task and finish” groups led by a Chief Officer </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and a member of my leadership t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">eam. It will</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> consist of a small team of subject matter experts and external stakeholders who will report back to the Commissioner’s Strategic Board, providing key recommendations to inform decision-making. Key to this approach will be the scrutiny of the c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">urrent set of measures and targets for each specific areas and the ability to propose new measures that will drive performance improvements.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Agreed areas for thematic review for years 2013/14 and 2014/15 include (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">) violence against women and girls, (ii</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">) hate crime, (iii) response to anti-social behaviour and (iv) equality and diversity.  The Joint Performance Management </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Group will</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> recommend further areas for review as and when needed.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Future targets will be based on the principles of:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Continuous and s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ustained improvement</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">An emphasis on the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">quality</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> of response  </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">relevant and purposeful indicators </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">providing a challenge to improve against peer forces and on a national basis</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">aligning with the period of the Police and Crime Reduction Plan, but evaluated </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">annually as part of the planning cycle to ensure relevance</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">With regard to crime recording practices, the current performance dashboard contains the latest </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Home Office National Crime Recording Standards</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> performance levels and these are discussed at the Joint Planning and Performance Group.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">On the wider partnership level I am able to monitor performance through regional forums such as Safer South Wales and the South Wales Criminal Justice Board. These fo</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rums provide opportunities to identify and share best practice across partner agencies but also provide further governance arrangements to test performance and provide an element of consistency in delivering services across </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">South Wales</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">How do you assure</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> yourself that the recorded crime figures for your area are correct? To what extent can you trust the crime statistics for your area? </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">There are a number of approaches I use to inform my overall assessment of the integrity of crime recording in South Wales</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. As mentioned above, performance</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> against the Home Office standards</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> is assessed at the monthly Joint Planning and Performance Board, prior to which this area is discussed at monthly </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">F</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">orce </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">CompStat</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> performance meetings. Any issues are then escalated to the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">monthly Strategic Commissioner’s Board. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In addition there are both internal and external audit mechanisms which are designed to ensure compliance and provide independent scrutiny. For example, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Crime Registry Unit</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> has been established by the Chief Consta</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ble.  Key functions of this unit are to monitor and check to ensure that crime recording complies with Home Office guidance and to give advice and guidance.  The unit </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">undertakes frequent audits on crime recording compliance</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">reports</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> findings to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">hief </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ficers.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I am also linking </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">with </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">HMIC</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to ensure that our respective oversight responsibilities complement each other.  I am aware that HMIC </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is currently undertaking an inspection on crime data integrity</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.  I shall give the findings careful consideration and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">agree with the Chief Constable appropriate monitoring arrangements in respect of any improvements required.   </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">January 2014</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>